#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""kyth-exe-handler — intercept Windows and RPM installers with KythOS guidance.

Registered as the default MIME handler for common Windows executable,
installer, and RPM package MIME types so that double-clicking a download in
Dolphin shows a curated suggestion dialog instead of silently failing or
teaching the wrong mutable-Fedora mental model.

Ticking "Always open Windows installers in Bottles" in the dialog persists
auto_bottles in ~/.config/kyth/exe-handler.conf; from then on .exe/.msi files
are handed straight to Bottles with no dialog (the dialog still appears if
Bottles is not installed). Pass --dialog to force the dialog back open and
untick the box, or edit/delete the config file.
"""

